# OWASP-oriented secure coding

When editing application code, actively check:

| Area | Do |
|------|----|
| Injection | Parameterized queries; never concatenate untrusted input into SQL/OS/commands |
| XSS | Context-appropriate encoding; avoid `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` unless strictly necessary and sanitized |
| Authn/Authz | Verify server-side; session fixation/expiry; IDOR via object ownership checks |
| CSRF | Tokens or same-site + framework defaults for state-changing requests |
| SSRF | Allowlist hosts/schemes; block metadata IPs; no raw user URL fetches without gates |
| Files | Validate type/size; store outside web root; random filenames |
| Crypto | Use vetted libraries; no custom crypto; keys from KMS/HSM patterns—not env in repo |
| Deserialization | Avoid unsafe pickle/YAML/`eval` on untrusted data |
| Errors | Generic messages to users; details only in server logs without secrets |

Prefer fixing root cause over adding brittle regex filters.
